{"word":"σταυρός","slug":"σταυρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>σταυρός, οῦ, ὁ</el></b> [<el>ἵστημι</el>; <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> focus on idea of standing]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘structure used in carrying out a death sentence’, <b>cross <a href='B:470 27:32'>Mt 27:32</a>, <a href='B:470 27:40'>40</a>, <a href='B:470 27:42'>42</a>; <a href='B:480 15:21'>Mk 15:21</a>; <a href='B:490 23:26'>Lk 23:26</a>; <a href='B:500 19:17'>J 19:17</a>, <a href='B:500 19:19'>19</a>, <a href='B:500 19:25'>25</a>, <a href='B:500 19:31'>31</a>; <a href='B:570 2:8'>Phil 2:8</a>; <a href='B:580 1:20'>Col 1:20</a>; <a href='B:650 12:2'>Hb 12:2</a>.</b> The <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ metaph.\">metaph.</a> use in <b><a href='B:470 10:38'>Mt 10:38</a>; <a href='B:470 16:24'>16:24</a></b> forms a bridge to<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> by metonymy, in sense of Jesus Christ’s well-known crucifixion experience, <b>the cross, <a href='B:530 1:17'>1 Cor 1:17f</a>; <a href='B:550 5:11'>Gal 5:11</a>; <a href='B:550 6:12'>6:12</a>, <a href='B:550 6:14'>14</a>; <a href='B:560 2:16'>Eph 2:16</a>; <a href='B:570 3:18'>Phil 3:18</a>; <a href='B:580 2:14'>Col 2:14</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:στατήρ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:σταυρόω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}